  mcq:{q:"Why do interviewers ask which vSphere version you've used?", options:["To test your typing speed","To gauge how current and specific your hands-on experience is","Because version numbers are a trick question","To check your internet connection"], answer:1, explain:"Version-specific questions help interviewers assess real, current hands-on experience rather than generic familiarity."},
  summary:["vSphere is VMware's virtualization suite (ESXi + vCenter).","This answer is personal-experience based — state your real versions.","Source example experience: vSphere 7.0 and 8.0.","Version knowledge signals how current your skills are.","Major versions bring new features, APIs, and security changes.","Always be ready to name 1-2 features unique to the version you claim."]
