  summary:["Linux has two main modes: Graphical (GUI) and Command Line (CLI).","Both modes run the same underlying Linux system.","GUI mode includes a full visual desktop environment.","CLI mode is text-only, accessed via terminal or SSH.","Servers typically run CLI-only to conserve resources.","This connects to the \"Minimal\" install choice covered in Q19."]
