  "snapshot": "A saved state of a VM's disk, memory, and settings that you can revert back to.",
  "datastore": "Where VM files (disks, configs) are stored — like a folder for virtual hard drives.",
  "VLAN": "A virtual local network that logically separates traffic on shared physical hardware.",
  "DRS": "Distributed Resource Scheduler — VMware's automatic load-balancer for VMs across hosts.",
  "iLO": "HP's remote management chip for accessing a server's console without being physically present.",
  "iDRAC": "Dell's equivalent of iLO — remote management access built into the server hardware.",
  "systemd": "The modern service manager that starts, stops, and monitors Linux background services.",
  "vCenter": "VMware's centralized dashboard for managing many ESXi hosts and VMs from one place.",
  "ESXi": "VMware's Type 1 (bare-metal) hypervisor that runs directly on server hardware.",
  "open-source": "Source code that's publicly available for anyone to view, use, or modify.",
